id1: JAPEX Abalone-1 Final Well Report — Drilling

id5: Abalone—l was drilled in the southwestern portion of the AC/P 29 permit in 81.7 days for a total cost of AU$22.4 million.

id6: Drilling operations exceeded the planned drilling time by 13.7 days. The extra days required to drill Abalone—l was due in part to the higher than anticipated pore pressure. The higher pore pressure also resulted in the well not reaching its final TD nor intersecting the Echuca Shoals objective.

id7: The well was plugged and abandoned.
